{
  "texts": [
    "All models were trained for five epochs, with peak performance typically achieved within the first three epochs.",
    "Using the estimated models, we make predictions for the hold-out test sample and evaluate performance.",
    "9 The 21 models achieved an average AUROC of 0.82, ranging from 0.80 to 0.84 across yearly models.",
    "Similarly, we analyze model performance by scientific field, finding that Health Sciences and Physical Sciences achieve the highest AUROC scores, while Chemical Sciences and Information and Communication Sciences score lower.",
    "10 We tested various hyper-parameters to identify the training configuration with the highest out-of-sample performance."
  ]
}